    "recap_url": "https://uncbears.com/news/2026/3/9/baseball-northern-colorado-drops-series-finale-in-orem-prepares-for-first-home-series-hosting-st-thomas",
    "recap_headline": "University of Northern Colorado Athletics",
    "recap_text": "OREM, Utah\n\u2013 Northern Colorado closed its series against Utah Valley with a 5\u20131 loss on Monday afternoon at UCCU Ballpark. The Bears collected seven hits in the contest, but a five-run fifth inning from Utah Valley proved to be the difference.\nNorthern Colorado starter\nLucas Stone\ndelivered a strong outing early, keeping the Wolverines off the scoreboard through four innings. Stone scattered just two hits while striking out four and allowing no walks.The Bears broke through first in the fourth inning.\nZeke Minic\nsparked the offense with a double and later came around to score, giving Northern Colorado a 1\u20130 lead. The Bears finished the afternoon with seven hits, including two from Minic and two from\nEthan Fillinger\n.\nUtah Valley answered in the bottom of the fifth inning. The Wolverines strung together several hits to plate five runs and flip the momentum of the game.\nNorthern Colorado turned to\nBrady Hudson\nin relief, who took the loss after the fifth-inning surge.\nJax Pfister\nand\nLogan Borboa\nfollowed out of the bullpen, combining to hold the Wolverines scoreless over the final 2.1 innings.\nMinic led the Bears offensively with two hits and the team's lone extra-base hit, while Fillinger added two singles.\nBrandon Sanchez\n,\nLogan Pruski\nand\nBrett Barber\neach contributed a hit.\nON DECK:\nNorthern Colorado returns home for the first time this season to host the St. Thomas Tommie's and open conference play with a three-game series at Jackson Field. The series opener and the Bears home opener is scheduled for Friday at 2:05 p.m. MDT.\nDIAMOND CLUB\nThe Diamond Club plays a vital role in supporting the UNC Baseball program. By giving to the Diamond Club, you help provide access to facility enhancements\u2014such as the Jackson Field Turf Project\u2014along with advanced technology and elevated daily operations, giving our student-athletes the resources to compete and excel at the highest level.\nGive to the Diamond Club today!\nFOLLOW THE BEARS\nFor complete coverage of UNC Athletics, visit uncbears.com. Follow the baseball team on X (formerly Twitter) (@UNC_BearsBSB) and Instagram (@UNC_BearsBaseball)."
